fields.transit: The Broadway Station for the N/Q Subway is less than 5 minutes walking distance from my place and runs 24/7. Getting anywhere in Manhattan is a breeze. A quick 15 minute ride will put you right by Central Park, Times Square, Upper East Side, and other popular destinations. The line will also take you right into the middle of Herald Square, Union Square, Soho, Chinatown, and more. It's an amazing subway line to be near. The N/Q subway lines also gets you to all sorts of other subways/transit hubs including The Port Authority, Grand Central Station, and Penn Station. You can buy your subway metrocards at the station. Free street parking by the house.  LGA Airport is a quick 20 minute / 20 taxi ride. There's a bus/train from LGA as well. JFK is a quick 25-30 minute / 45 Taxi ride. By public transportation it's a little over an hour and the subway is less than 6 blocks from our place. (Steinway Station stop)

fields.neighborhood_overview: Battery Park is clean, fresh and green. The space is super quiet, and the summer is cool and amazing down here. You have a view of trees, hear birds in the morning, and are right by the water. There's a new food court that just opened steps from here with plenty of gourmet options. There are 4 super markets including a Whole Foods within minutes walking distance. There's also a new high-end shopping center. Steps from the new WTC memorial, or the Hudson river and parks, there's plenty of things to do, and ways to enjoy this revitalized area.

fields.host_about:
Friendly, fun, and occasionally funny, I grew up in New York, work as a software product designer, and when I don't want to make money, I teach yoga and meditation.

I live in green and clean Battery Park City—a great escape from main Manhattan—but still close to everything by train. 

I eat vegetarian, keep houseplants, and practice meditation at home every day. My passions are also traveling, and connecting with people.

I hope you can come and enjoy my cozy home—the room has a lot of great vibrations, which I share kindly with you.

The apartment gets amazing light with south exposures.  It is an easy walk to Riverside Park (2 blocks), subways, shopping, CitiBike.
